ic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Critical Strike: the way it SHOULD work?</span><hr size=1> I've been thinking about the way CS works and how many assassins use it for every-day melee. I was thinking Critical Strike should be just that, massive strikes that inflict deadly blows at high cost to the assassin.<br>
<br>
Ponder this: if CS did 2 or 3x the damage it does now, but cost 3-4x the endurance, would it be more in line with the way most of us wish to play our classes?<br>
<br>
If the PA/CD/SS chain took ALL our endurance, but each style did 2-3x what they do now..<br>
<br>
If Garrote/AH did 2-3x what they do now, but we could only throw about 3 or 4 of them...<br>
<br>
This would make the normal melee styles useful,and make our CS moves &quot;finishing blows&quot; or &quot;crippling attacks&quot; as many of us would like them to be.<br>
<br>
thoughts?<br>
<br>
X <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/unandurius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nandurius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/5/02 9:24:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3691.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ccs.neu.edu/home/phaas/phazer-avatar.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Critical Strike: the way it SHOULD work?</span><hr size=1> Not sure what game you're playing, but that's what crit strikes already does. No way there should be a damage increase. If there's something that needs to be looked at, it's how close you hit to the maximum damage cap, since it seems pretty much impossible to hit for more than 40-50% of the cap on epic armor. Then again, you really shouldn't be able to two-shot level 50's, so I guess killing in 3 hit's will have to do for now :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/5/02 9:24:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3691.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> It would probally massivly overpower critblades, considering they would have an approximate 3300 perf cap <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uanduinlejeune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anduin Le Jeune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/5/02 10:05:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3691.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Psh, if anything needs to be looked at, it's the insane amount of damage Shadowblades do with two handed weapons.  I hear them whining about Left Axe, and frankly I don't see why any of them would bother with it any more than Infiltrators would with dual wield.<br>
<br>
I spend quite a bit of time in Caledonia, and in my various dealings with SBs I've come to realize a few things as simple realities.  I'm level 34 currently and most of the SBs are level 35.  I maxed my dual wield, stupid me.  <br>
<br>
1) If they crit me before I them, I'm dead.  They crit for at least 630 damage, each individual is very consistent in their damage (plus or minus 20 damage).  I get the impression that they DO hit near or right on their cap every perf vs. a blue Infiltrator)  For a frame of reference, I hit blue con players wearing chain (weak to thrust weapons) for 320 damage MAX.<br>
<br>
2) An orange con SB can do twice as much damage with a non-crit style than I can do with a perfectly executed perf. This isn't extra critical damage.  They do it on every hit.  Trust me, this is something I'm overly familiar with.<br>
<br>
An example of the best-case scenario drag-em-out brawl with an SB:<br>
<br>
I find Jarran wandering alone on the battlegrounds.  He sucks, so I perf him, around 130 to 150 damage, off-hand weapon does another 13 damage.  Two poisons successfully applied.  His blinks and casually opens with some unknown axe style.  The one he always uses, for around 270 damage.  I swing both weapons two more times, around 20 to 30 damage on main weapon, 10 to 20 on offhand.  He's at about two thirds life.  He swings again, another 270 damage.  One more round of that, he's still got more than half of his HPs, I'm dead with about 150 damage overkill.  Of course, I never hang around anymore so that he can do this damage.  I'm not stupid =)<br>
<br>
Everyone in Albion, irrespective of class, reports insane amounts of damage from these freaks of nature.  Why Mythic has decided to let one class remain the one-shot crit masters of the game is beyond me.  I rather like how my class has turned out.  I don't think giving me a two-handed weapon would be reasonably fair to any of the people I battle with every night.  I need ideal conditions for a clean kill that will take 3 or 4 rounds of hits, and that gives them a sporting chance to survive if they didn't run far out of range of any assistance.  This is rediculous folks.  Everyone but an SB will tell you the same.  I'm sure they love slaughtering people like cattle, but it gets a little old when you're on the receiving end. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uaiden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aiden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/5/02 10:21:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3691.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> once you grow up to be a big infil then you can say how good or bad critblades are. until then,its rather silly to equate how good a critblade is to the joke that levels 0-35 are.<br>
<br>
critblades are absurdly easy to defeat,for other rogues. <br>
<br>
they also wont one shot in most cases as they get to 40+,yes it can happen but generally not against even con players.<br>
