</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/5/02 11:20:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3691.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Crit blades arent overpowered, anymore.<br>
<br>
There was a time... way back pre 1.50... but that's long gone.  Now they are just like normal rogues with a slow 2h sword (not that 2h is bad).  Evade fixes and realm skill points, as well as epic armor and one shot nerf pretty much destroyed any crit spec person.<br>
<br>
And people complaining about not being able to kill oranges have issues - seek help.  Yellows, I can see if its a 50/50 thing, blues and lower is justified by captain obvious, but oranges - no way.<br>
<br>
And really, just to pick at somethings in the previous post, Its not too hard to land a CD with the improved /stick and snare poison, even with a slow weapon (actually it gives more time for stick to work)<br>
<br>
